Suggested practice:

Exercise 1

Ask a chatbot to propose translations of an idiom and ask the chatbot to identify similar idioms in the target language. You can start with a language that you are more familiar with, then try this with a language that you are less familiar with and see if you can still prompt the chatbot to give a good translation. If you have a friend who speaks the target language, ask them what they think of the result!

Some idioms that you can try:

“every cloud has a silver lining”, “it’s a piece of cake!”, “I let the cat out of the bag”, “I’m on the same page”, “I bit off more than I can chew”.


